Durban - People on social media have welcomed the resignation of Eskom’s Chief Financial Officer Anoj Singh. His resignation was tended in on Monday. “The board of Eskom, through the Chairman, has accepted the resignation and communicated the acceptance through Mr Singh’s attorneys. Mr Singh’s resignation is with immediate effect,” the company said in a statement. Here are some of the tweets that welcomed the resignation and wanted further steps to be taken against him. This comes as the company is dealing with scandals that have affected the parastatal. Singh’s resignation comes in the wake of the parastatal chairman Zethembe Khoza who quit a few days ago. His resignation was also welcomed by many on Twitter. This comes as this past weekend government announced a new board for the state owned enterprise which will have Jabu Mabuza as the new chairman. Here is some of the reaction to Singh’s resignation: 